workflow.name: Qualify real estate leads via SMS with GPT-4o, Twilio, and Google Sheets
workflow.description:
## üè° AI-Powered Real Estate Lead Qualifier (n8n Workflow)

## Description
This n8n workflow automates lead engagement and qualification for real estate buyers. When someone submits a form on your real estate website, the system instantly responds via SMS, starting a conversation powered by an AI Agent. The AI asks pre-qualifying questions (like budget, location, and timeline), logs the entire conversation, and then summarizes and sends the lead info to a real estate agent. Chat history is stored in a PostgreSQL database (via Supabase) and tied to each buyer's phone number.

## Key Features
üì© Instant SMS Response: Follows up immediately after form submission.

ü§ñ AI Chat-Based Qualification: Conversational agent gathers buyer needs and preferences.

üóÇ Supabase Chat Memory: Stores chat history tied to the buyer‚Äôs phone number to maintain context.

üìä Lead Summary & Agent Handoff: Summarizes conversation and logs it to Google Sheets for the agent.

üîÅ Customizable AI Questions: Easily edit the questions asked by the AI to suit your process.

parameters.content:
## AI-Powered Real Estate Lead Responder & Qualifier (n8n Workflow)

** Feel free to contact me if you need help implementing (rbreen@ynteractive.com) **

## How to Implement
Follow these steps to get your workflow fully running:

1. Sign Up for Twilio
üëâ https://login.twilio.com/

Purchase a phone number with SMS support.

In n8n, set up Twilio credentials and connect them to the Twilio nodes in the workflow.

2. Add Your OpenAI API Key
üëâ https://platform.openai.com/

Get your secret key.

Add your key to the AI Agent and Chat Model nodes using OpenAI credentials.

3. Set Up Google Sheets
üëâ Copy this sheet - https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1jSlYXSBA9BJvSuMiqFUJo3omztNJtbejNYEopfbGWN8/edit?usp=sharing

In n8n, connect your Google Sheets OAuth2 credentials and update the sheet ID in the Google Sheets nodes.

4. Set Up Supabase for Chat Memory
üëâ https://supabase.com/

Create a free Supabase project.

Go to Database > Connection Info, and copy your PostgreSQL credentials.

In n8n, go to Credentials > PostgreSQL and create a new connection using your Supabase info.

Link this credential in the PostgreSQL Chat Memory field of your AI Agent node to persist and recall chat history per phone number.

5. Customize Buyer Questions (Optional)
Edit the AI Agent node that asks pre-qualifying questions.

You can change the prompt to ask any questions relevant to your lead funnel (e.g., loan preapproval, desired move-in date, etc.).

‚úÖ Ready to Launch!
Once configured:

The workflow listens for a form submission.

Sends an SMS to the buyer to start a chat.

Uses AI to ask key buyer questions.

Stores chat memory in Supabase (so follow-ups stay contextual).

Summarizes and logs the lead to Google Sheets for your agent.

The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
